Keith Isdale 9th June 2018 <keithisdale@gmail.com>
    4.6.1
    Fixes
        Fix walking, tracing command logic.
	Output of templates command when multiple XSLT documents are present
        Correct logic that guesses relative XSLT file path given to 'break' command (needed debugging http/ftp documents)
        Correct logic of output of 'templates' command with '-q' option
        Remove useless 'this' option to 'templates' command
    Features
        To improve UI in qxslbg emit XsldbgDebuggerBase::completeTransform() signal when completed XSLT tranformation
        'entities' command output now in two new forms with "<ID>"values now quoted
            Enties PublicID:"<ID>" SystemID:"<ID>"
            Enties SystemID:"<ID>"
        'entities' command output now support '-r' argument that prints resolved URI for entity
            Enties PublicID:"<ID>" SystemID:"<ID>" URI:"<URI>"
            Enties SystemID:"<ID>" URI:"<URI>"
        Update XsldbgDebuggerBase to emit the resolved URI of entities
        Add tests for walk and trace commands
	Add test for http:// and ftp:// XML/XSLT document paths
	Only print "Reached template" when XSLT match or mode has changed
	Sort breakpoints by ID
        Sort templates by file and line number
        The <match> option to 'templates' command will match template whose name *contains* <match>

